South Africa to Raise Gasoline Price 2.9% as Crude Climbs, Department Says

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-04-28T11:04:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/south-africa-to-raise-gasoline-price-2-9-as-crude-climbs-department-says.html
South Africa  will increase the
price of gasoline by 2.9 percent on May 4 after crude oil prices
surged, the  Department of Energy  said.  Gasoline will rise 29 cents to 10.25 rand a liter in
Gauteng province, while diesel will increase as much as 16 cents
a liter, the department said in an e-mailed statement today.
Kerosene prices are due to rise as much as 20 cents a liter,
while the price of liquified petroleum gas will jump as much as
53 cents a kilogram, the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nasreen Seria at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net  